        "TextSection": {
            "TextSectionType": "Definition",
            "Contents": "A life-threatening rapidly progressive thrombotic disorder affecting mainly neonates and children that is characterized by purpuric skin lesions and disseminated intravascular coagulation. It may progress rapidly to multi-organ failure caused by thrombotic occlusion of small and medium-sized blood vessels. There are two forms of the disorder that are classified according to triggering mechanisms: acute infectious (the most common form) and idiopathic purpura fulminans."
        },
